"Abstract Tales from the Crypt is now one year old! This periodic series of articles on topics in international cryptography policy recently celebrated its first year of regular monthly publication in the pages of Computer Fraud & Security with the May 2000 edition of the journal. After a one-month pause in June, the column now moves to a bimonthly format. The author’s association with the Computer Fraud & Security Bulletin actually goes back over a decade to when Tina Monk was its editor and the ITSEC was under development (see Part 8, January 2000). Subsequently, I joined the Editorial Advisory Board and contributed a number of short pieces during Helen Meyer’s period as editor. The arrival of Sandy Nichol in the editorial chair coincided — purely by chance — with my departure from the Infosec Unit at the European Commission and I became much freer to write more expansively on a subject that has occupied my interest for much of my working life."
